    "body": "At this point, if the bot is disconnected it either exists with uncaught error:\r\n\r\n      events.js:85\r\n            throw er; // Unhandled 'error' event\r\n                  ^\r\n      Error: connect ECONNREFUSED\r\n          at exports._errnoException (util.js:746:11)\r\n          at TCPConnectWrap.afterConnect [as oncomplete] (net.js:1010:19)\r\n\r\n\r\nor it just stops dispatching events and doesn't even notice it's out of the game. Obviously what I want from a bot is to be as stable as possible, so I don't have to babysit it every few minutes. So, in general, I think there's a need for better handling of disconnects.",
